What’s happening at THS?

Mr. Brigance’s classes had fun participating in a lab where they made paper towers by applying physics to see who could make the tallest tower! Haley Kessler, Zoey Wallace, Natalie Whitley and Halle Stone won with a tower that reached a height of 8ft 1inch tall!

post_text:
👋🏽 Hey THS Parents, Students & Bulldog Community! 👋🏽

🎓 Graduation ceremonies will take place tomorrow, May 22nd at 8:00PM in Bulldog Stadium. Each graduating Senior has been issued tickets for family to participate as spectators. Graduation will be live streamed for those unable to attend. The links will be posted on the Tahoka ISD website & app tomorrow. Please note we will follow all guidelines regarding COVID-19 & social distancing. PPE will be issued for Seniors & guests participating in the ceremony. For your health & safety please follow all guidelines set forth by the Governor regarding social distancing as we honor our Tahoka Bulldog Seniors on this graduation night. 🎓

🐾💙 We look forward to celebrating the THS Class of 2020! 💙🐾

Thank you all & have a great evening!

post_text:
🎉❗️Important Update regarding the Graduation Celebration Parade❗️🎉

🐾 Seniors and Tahoka Bulldog Community: 🐾

We will celebrate our Senior Graduating Class with a Celebration Parade Thursday, May 21st at 7:00PM. Our parade will start on Bulldog Lane (North 4th Street by the gymnasium) and proceed east to Main street and south to the conclusion at the court house. Please make plans to make noise for this graduating Class of 2020 as we honor their accomplishments.

Seniors you will need to report to the parade start by 6:30PM for line-up with a designated adult driver in your cap and gowns. If any Senior needs a vehicle/driver for the parade please contact the high school at 806-561-4538 and we will arrange one for you!

We will honor our graduates the next day with graduation ceremonies starting at 8:00PM at Bulldog Stadium.

post_text:
❗️Reminder Parents and Students❗️

Tahoka ISD is furnishing free meals each day to ALL students. Parents may drive to the back of the cafeteria and a pickup point will be established. We will ask for the names of the children you are picking up food for and bring the food out to you. If you have students in multiple grade levels we will give the meals at one time to avoid a second trip. If parents have no way of picking up the food, we will deliver the food on your request. Please call 806-561-4350 if you need this assistance.

Parents are asked to pick up the food according to the following schedule:

Pre-K thru 1st Grade: 11:00 AM - 11:30 AM
2nd thru 3rd Grade: 11:30 AM - 12:00 PM
4th thru 5th Grade: 12:00 PM - 12:30 PM
6th thru 12th Grade: 12:30 PM

Don’t forget to check out the Tahoka ISD website and mobile app for any updates!

This past weekend, FCCLA officers and members attended the Region I FCCLA competitive events and leadership conference in Lubbock. We have 4 events and 2 individual competitions headed to state!

Nina Arriazola, Abegail Bernal, and Danalyn Garcia placed 3rd in Interior Design.

Alex Perez placed 2nd in Say Yes to FCS.

Dylan Quintero placed 2nd in Sports Nutrition.

Patricia Camargo placed 2nd in Teach and Train.

Meah Vera and Hope Quintero both received gold medals with their FCS Assessment scores.

Congratulations Tahoka FCCLA on a successful weekend!

post_text: ❗️ATTENTION DUAL CREDIT STUDENTS❗️
shared_text:
Tahoka HS/MS Counseling
February 3 at 3:38 PM ·

Attention Dual Credit Students:

Just a reminder that dual credit students enrolled in online courses at South Plains College have access to free, online tutoring via Tutor.com.

Students may be able to access Tutor.com from the "Content Area" of their Blackboard course, but can also access the service through the main landing page in Blackboard, after logging in with their SPC username and password. Once they have logged in and have accessed Tutor.com, students will simply select the subject area that interests them.

Students will have access to Tutor.com during the following hours - from 8:00 P.M. – 8:00 AM, Monday through Thursday and then all weekend from 6:00 PM on Friday through 8:00 AM on Monday. Though these times may look odd, these were the hours most frequented by our students last semester.

For the time being, students will be limited to 1.5 hours per week with online tutors. If a student needs additional hours, only rare exceptions will be made - they're welcome to contact myself or Cody Thackerson (SPC's Academic Support Coordinator) and request additional time

Cristal Burse shared a link to the group: Tahoka 3-D Band Parents.
July 29, 2019 at 1:30 PM ·

Hello 3D band families! Please share!

As mentioned here before, the state of Texas has gone an extra mile to ensure the safety of our students participating in any physical activity by requiring a physical.

The Family Wellness Clinic will offer physicals for us for $20 on Wednesday, July 31, from 1:00-3:30. A parent signature is required before the physical is performed.

Alternatively, the Covenant Healthcare Clinic in Plainview will do them free of charge if you’re interested.

Any student entering year 1 or 3 of high school must have a physical examination signed by a physician and on file with the district before being able to participate in any type of marching practice.

The same goes…

post_text: The Tahoka High School Chapter of the National Honor Society will induct seven new members to its chapter tomorrow evening at 5:30. The ceremony will be held in the auditorium, and a brief reception will follow in the high school library. Parents, family, and TISD faculty are invited to share in celebrating this accomplishment with the new inductees. post_text:
💙🐾 THS Shattered Dreams has come to an end. Thank you to our students who stepped up in front of their peers, we know that may be difficult at times. Thank you to the THS staff who organized and put the program together so smoothly. Thank you to all the men, women, community leaders and sponsors who put so much work and effort to make this all possible for our students. Also, thank you to our guest speakers Brett Parker and Lanae Gwin for opening up and sharing their life experiences and heartache. We hope this is an eye opener. If different choices are made and one life is saved because of this experience then our THS Shattered Dreams program was a SUCCESS! 🐾💙

📹 Video credit goes to Senior Jennifer Alonzo. Thank you Jennifer for all your hard work and time spent making the video so that we can all look back and reflect on such an important time for THS! 📹

🐾💙✏️📚This past Tuesday, the Tahoka UIL Academic team competed at the district meet in Plains. A total of 38 students participated and Tahoka placed in 10 events!

Rogelio Garcia placed 1st in Current Issues & Events and Molly Broun placed 3rd in News Writing. Rogelio and Molly have advanced to the Regional Meet in Odessa. In addition, Maribel Garcia placed 6th in Current Issues & Events, Karlie Swinford placed 6th in Copy Editing, Branyn Fluellen placed 6th in Editorial Writing, Molly Broun placed 5th in Feature Writing, Nathaniel Sullivan placed 4th and Alex Tew placed 6th in Headline Writing, Tristan Stice placed 6th in Mathematics, Callie Nevill placed 6th in Poetry Interpretation, Tamara Ramirez placed 5th in Prose Interpretation, and Major Due placed 6th in Social Studies.

We are so proud of the hard work and effort these students put in and we wish good luck to Rogelio and Molly at Regionals! 📚✏️💙🐾

Tahoka FCCLA has had a busy few days at the Region I FCCLA Conference in Odessa!

Joey Herrera was reelected as a Region Officer and will be serving as the Vice President of Parliamentary Law!

The Interior Design Team consisting of Dalton Chapman, Madison Moya, and Spring Garcia took home 2nd place and will be heading to the State Conference in Dallas!

Several individuals participated in taking FCS Assessments and received awards! Chris Vargas, Abegail Bernal, and Alex Perez all received silver medals and Adriana Gonzales received a bronze medal.

We are so proud of all of our students that competed this weekend and we are looking forward to state!

Reminder from our AD Coach Overstreet:

Bulldog Fans please read carefully. The UIL has a rule that states you can not go LIVE during games. You can record and post to social media later but you are prohibited from streaming live. PLEASE, PLEASE DO NOT go live. We and more importantly our student athletes can be punished if we violate this rule. I know it seems crazy in today’s world but let’s make sure we do our part to follow the rules so our kids don’t get punished. Hope to see everyone Tuesday night 7:30 at the Rip.

TISD Parents... I know many of you are concerned, as we all are, with a situation that occurred north of the elementary playground today. - Dick Van Hoose Superintendent Tahoka ISD

FFA officers were pushed outside of their comfort zone today while volunteering at the San Angelo Special Needs Livestock Show & Rodeo. Students were originally signed up to serve as livestock ambassadors but ended up teaching calf roping. Our students still had a valuable experience interacting and teaching special needs students who may never have the opportunity to experience the stock show way of life. What an awesome way to give back!

post_text:
Upcoming dates and information from the counselor:

The TSI will be given to all Juniors on February 12th at THS. Any Sophomore who wants to take dual credit courses next year will need the TSI in order to do so. Also any senior needing to re-take a section will also be able to test at this time. If you are a sophomore or senior, you must sign up in the counselor's office and pay a $16. fee. Juniors will not have to sign up or pay.

The ACT school day test will be given on February 20th at THS. All students who are already signed up should have gotten a letter about this in the mail. You will have to pay $40. by Friday, February 1st in order to be able to take the test here on campus. If you will have trouble paying, please see the counselor for your options.

All local scholarships will be handed out to all seniors on February 19th. The completed application packet will be due back to the counselor's office on March 5th.

Tahoka High School Cheerleading
January 11, 2019 at 9:24 PM ·

Please be aware there is a company that is asking for you to buy ads that will be placed on a type of drink container that our High School Cheerleaders will throw to the crowd at home football games. This is in no way connected with Tahoka Schools or our cheerleaders.

As a business owner it is your decision where and what to spend your advertising dollars on. If you choose to spend money on an out of town company and ask that we help with the distribution – we will do everything we can to accommodate you within the guidelines of the district. However, we are a small community with only so many businesses that we can go to for fundraising. We will help you in every way that we can. With that said, please consider staying local with advertising dollars as we move forward towards another new school year.

post_text:
🎼🎶 ATTENTION Band Parents 🎶🎼

This year's Christmas concerts have been rescheduled and relocated because construction on the auditorium has not been completed. A letter was sent home last week with your child.

The concert will be held on Thursday, December 13th starting at 6:00 pm in the high school gym and will be all grade levels on one night. 244 Performers total!

Middle School wears blue uniform top and black bottoms. High school wears Sunday best. Festive hats are welcome.

5th Grade: Meet in the band hall by 5:30. Go on stage at 5:45. Perform at 6:00.

6th Grade: Meet in the band hall by 5:45 when fifth grade leaves. Go on stage at 6:20 and start immediately.

7th Grade: Meet in the HIGH SCHOOL LIBRARY with instrument before 6:20. Go on stage at 6:40 and start immediately.

**Intermission***

8th-12th Grade: Assemble in the band hall starting at 7:15, go on stage at 7:25, begin at 7:30.

Remember, our concert counts as our final exam grade and absences are not permitted. Please let us know if you have questions!

AND please share!

Thanks!
Carroll Rhodes and Cristal Burse

From Coach Overstreet:

Senior Night Schedule

We will begin the Sr. Night festivities promptly at 6:20. We will go in the following order to allow everyone time to make sure they are ready for the 7pm kickoff: Football, Band, and Cheerleaders.

We will have 20 minutes to get through everyone because at 6:40 we must begin the UIL required pregame announcements. If you have any questions please feel free to ask, but we hope you come out and help us recognize these young people for all they have done for the Tahoka Family the last 4 years.

shared_text:
Tahoka High School
October 24, 2018 at 11:14 AM ·

Tahoka High School will be recognizing Veterans and Gold Star Veterans' families (families who have lost a loved one serving in the military) at the November 9, 2018 football game during halftime of the Tahoka Bulldogs vs. Smyer Bobcats game. Free admission for Veterans.

The National Honor Society and Student Council will be serving a meal for the Veterans and families at 6:15 at the Tahoka Cafeteria.

Please call the Tahoka High School office @ 806-561-4538 by November 8, 2018 if you plan on attending. Please give the following information when calling:

Name of Veteran
Branch served
Military Conflicts served
Where you are currently residing
